<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Lato:wght@300;400;600;700;800&family=Merriweather:ital,wght@0,400;1,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <style>
    @page {
      size: A4;
      margin: 0;
    }

    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
    }

    html, body {
      height: 297mm;
      width: 210mm;
      font-family: {{customization.fontFamily}};
      color: #333;
      line-height: 1.6;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .page {
      height: 297mm;
      width: 210mm;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      background: #FFFDF9;
    }

    /* Header */
    .header {
      padding: 10mm 18mm;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #37474F 0%, #263238 100%);
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .header::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      top: -30%;
      right: -10%;
      width: 40%;
      height: 160%;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
      transform: rotate(15deg);
    }

    .header-icon {
      font-size: 32px;
      margin-bottom: 3mm;
    }

    .header-title {
      font-size: 28px;
      font-weight: 800;
      color: white;
      margin-bottom: 2mm;
    }

    .header-subtitle {
      font-size: 12px;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
      font-family: 'Merriweather', Georgia, serif;
      font-style: italic;
    }

    /* Content */
    .content {
      flex: 1;
      padding: 10mm 18mm;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 6mm;
    }

    /* Mistake card */
    .mistake-card {
      background: white;
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 5mm 6mm;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.04);
      border: 1px solid #F0F0F0;
      display: flex;
      gap: 5mm;
      position: relative;
    }

    .mistake-number {
      width: 12mm;
      height: 12mm;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #EF5350 0%, #C62828 100%);
      border-radius: 50%;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: 800;
      color: white;
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }

    .mistake-content {
      flex: 1;
    }

    .mistake-title {
      font-size: 13px;
      font-weight: 800;
      color: #C62828;
      margin-bottom: 2mm;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 2mm;
    }

    .mistake-title-icon {
      font-size: 14px;
    }

    .mistake-text {
      font-family: 'Merriweather', Georgia, serif;
      font-size: 10px;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: #444;
    }

    .mistake-text strong {
      color: #333;
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    /* Lesson learned badge */
    .lesson {
      margin-top: 3mm;
      padding: 2.5mm 4mm;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #E8F5E9 0%, #C8E6C9 100%);
      border-radius: 6px;
      border-left: 3px solid #43A047;
      display: flex;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 2mm;
    }

    .lesson-icon {
      font-size: 12px;
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }

    .lesson-text {
      font-size: 9px;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #2E7D32;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }

    /* Footer */
    .page-footer {
      padding: 4mm 18mm;
      background: #F5F5F5;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
      font-size: 9px;
      color: #888;
    }

    .page-number {
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #666;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <div class="page">
    <div class="header">
      <div class="header-icon">üö´</div>
      <h1 class="header-title">Mistakes I Made</h1>
      <p class="header-subtitle">So you don't have to make them yourself</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content">
      <!-- Mistake 1: Alcohol -->
      <div class="mistake-card">
        <div class="mistake-number">1</div>
        <div class="mistake-content">
          <div class="mistake-title">
            <span class="mistake-title-icon">üç∫</span>
            Thinking alcohol didn't make a difference
          </div>
          <div class="mistake-text">
            Every other Friday, we'd get together with friends for dinner and a few beers. Nothing excessive. But I started noticing a pattern. On Sundays after a Friday of drinking, my legs felt heavier during easy runs, and I'd often cut the session short due to fatigue. On Sundays following a beer-free Friday? I'd finish my planned session without any issues. <strong>Once again, my body was telling me what didn't work for it.</strong>
          </div>
          <div class="lesson">
            <span class="lesson-icon">‚úì</span>
            <span class="lesson-text">Even moderate alcohol consumption affects recovery and performance days later. Listen to the patterns.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Mistake 2: Racing fasted -->
      <div class="mistake-card">
        <div class="mistake-number">2</div>
        <div class="mistake-content">
          <div class="mistake-title">
            <span class="mistake-title-icon">üç≥</span>
            Racing on an empty stomach
          </div>
          <div class="mistake-text">
            On race days, I'd start early and run fasted, afraid of feeling heavy. I could finish races this way, sure. But the difference was night and day when I started eating a <strong>light breakfast 90 minutes to 2 hours before competing</strong>. The performance improvement was massive‚Äîmore energy, better pacing, stronger finish.
          </div>
          <div class="lesson">
            <span class="lesson-icon">‚úì</span>
            <span class="lesson-text">Your body needs fuel. A light, practiced pre-race meal is essential for peak performance.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Mistake 3: Hydration -->
      <div class="mistake-card">
        <div class="mistake-number">3</div>
        <div class="mistake-content">
          <div class="mistake-title">
            <span class="mistake-title-icon">üíß</span>
            Only drinking when thirsty
          </div>
          <div class="mistake-text">
            For a long time, I only hydrated when I felt thirsty. Big mistake. <strong>By the time you feel thirst, you're already dehydrated</strong>, and it takes your body much longer to recover than if you had maintained preventive hydration throughout the day.
          </div>
          <div class="lesson">
            <span class="lesson-icon">‚úì</span>
            <span class="lesson-text">Hydrate consistently throughout the day‚Äîdon't wait for thirst to tell you it's too late.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Mistake 4: Improvising -->
      <div class="mistake-card">
        <div class="mistake-number">4</div>
        <div class="mistake-content">
          <div class="mistake-title">
            <span class="mistake-title-icon">‚ö†Ô∏è</span>
            Improvising the night before a race
          </div>
          <div class="mistake-text">
            A rookie mistake. There's a simple rule: <strong>nothing new on race day</strong>. No new clothes, no new shoes, no changes to your preparation or nutrition. I learned this the hard way‚Äîit was probably my worst race ever. Stomach cramps and heavy legs from the very start, all because I decided to "try something different" the night before.
          </div>
          <div class="lesson">
            <span class="lesson-icon">‚úì</span>
            <span class="lesson-text">Race day is not for experiments. Test everything during training. Stick to what works.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="page-footer">
      <span>Fuel Like a Runner ‚Ä¢ Learning from mistakes</span>
      <span class="page-number">Page {{pageNumber}}</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>

</html>
